### Politics

Given that Clark County holds most of Nevada's population, it heavily influences statewide elections. It generally leans Democratic, especially in presidential elections. The last Republican to win the county was [George H. W. Bush](/George_H._W._Bush) in 1988. However, it's not a monolithic Democratic bloc; the Republican candidate has consistently garnered at least 39% of the vote since 1996. [Donald Trump](/Donald_Trump) came closest to winning it in 2024, with 47.81%.

Republican presidential candidates have only carried the county six times since 1912, all during significant national Republican landslides.

Statewide, however, Clark County is more of a swing county. Several Republican [gubernatorial](/Gubernatorial) candidates and U.S. Senators have won it since the late 1980s. [John Ensign](/John_Ensign) was the last Republican senator to win the county in 2006, even as [Jim Gibbons](/Jim_Gibbons_(U.S._politician)) lost it in his gubernatorial win that same year. [Kenny Guinn](/Kenny_Guinn) and [Brian Sandoval](/Brian_Sandoval) both carried the county in their gubernatorial victories. [Joe Lombardo](/Joe_Lombardo), the current sheriff, lost the county by 5.7% in his 2022 gubernatorial win.

In 2018, [Dean Heller](/Dean_Heller) won 15 out of Nevada's 17 county-level jurisdictions in his Senate race, but [Jacky Rosen](/Jacky_Rosen) won Clark County by over 92,000 votes, nearly doubling her statewide margin. Similarly, in the 2018 gubernatorial election, [Steve Sisolak](/Steve_Sisolak) lost 15 out of 17 county-level jurisdictions but won Clark County by enough to secure the governorship. Between 2008 and 2024, the Democratic presidential candidate's margin in Clark County was enough to carry Nevada, a trend that broke in 2024 when Trump won the state despite losing the county.

The city of Las Vegas itself leans Democratic, as do Paradise, Spring Valley, and Enterprise. North Las Vegas, Sunrise Manor, Winchester, and Whitney are even more strongly Democratic. Henderson and Summerlin South lean Republican. Boulder City, where gambling is prohibited, is firmly Republican. Outside the Las Vegas Valley, the county tends Republican.

#### Regional Agencies

*   The [Clark County Regional Flood Control District](/Clark_County_Regional_Flood_Control_District) (CCRFCD), established in 1985, addresses flooding issues.
*   The [Regional Transportation Commission of Southern Nevada](/Regional_Transportation_Commission_of_Southern_Nevada) runs [RTC Transit](/RTC_Transit) and plans major roadways.
*   The [Southern Nevada Water Authority](/Southern_Nevada_Water_Authority) manages water distribution for the Las Vegas Valley.
*   The Las Vegas Wash Coordination Committee manages the [Las Vegas Wash](/Las_Vegas_Wash), having planted over 15,000 plants to stabilize its banks and removed over 500,000 pounds (230,000 kg) of trash.

#### State Government

The [Grant Sawyer State Office Building](/Grant_Sawyer), housing state government branches, is in Las Vegas. The [Nevada Department of Corrections](/Nevada_Department_of_Corrections) operates three prisons in Clark County: [High Desert State Prison](/High_Desert_State_Prison_(Nevada)) and [Southern Desert Correctional Center](/Southern_Desert_Correctional_Center) near [Indian Springs, Nevada](/Indian_Springs,_Nevada). The [Florence McClure Women's Correctional Center](/Florence_McClure_Women%27s_Correctional_Center) is in [North Las Vegas](/North_Las_Vegas), housing the state's female death row.

### Education

The [Clark County School District](/Clark_County_School_District) serves the entire county, with 228 elementary, 59 middle, and 54 high schools. It's the [fifth largest in the country](/List_of_the_largest_school_districts_in_the_United_States_by_enrollment), with 324,093 students in 2014. The old [Las Vegas High School](/Las_Vegas_High_School) building now houses the [Las Vegas Academy of Performing Arts](/Las_Vegas_Academy_of_the_Arts).

Higher education institutions include [University of Nevada, Las Vegas](/University_of_Nevada,_Las_Vegas) (UNLV), [College of Southern Nevada](/College_of_Southern_Nevada), [Nevada State University](/Nevada_State_University), [Roseman University of Health Sciences](/Roseman_University_of_Health_Sciences), and [Touro University Nevada](/Touro_University_Nevada).

### Transportation

#### Public Transit

[RTC Transit](/RTC_Transit), operated by the [Regional Transportation Commission of Southern Nevada](/Regional_Transportation_Commission_of_Southern_Nevada), provides public transit. [The Deuce](/The_Deuce_(transit_bus_service)) is their [Bus rapid transit](/Bus_rapid_transit) service connecting [Downtown Las Vegas](/Downtown_Las_Vegas) and the [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip).

#### Major Highways

*   [I-11](/Interstate_11)
*   [I-15](/Interstate_15_in_Nevada)
*   [I-215](/Las_Vegas_Beltway)
*   [US 93](/U.S._Route_93_in_Nevada)
*   [US 95](/U.S._Route_95_in_Nevada)
*   Numerous State Routes (SR) including [SR 146](/Nevada_State_Route_146) through [SR 613](/Nevada_State_Route_613).
*   [CC 215](/Clark_County_215) (also known as the Las Vegas Beltway)

#### Rail

[Amtrak](/Amtrak) service used to run through [Las Vegas station](/Las_Vegas_Union_Plaza_station) on the [Desert Wind](/Desert_Wind) line until 1997. Now, there's Amtrak Thruway service connecting to the [Southwest Chief](/Southwest_Chief). The [Las Vegas Monorail](/Las_Vegas_Monorail) operates on the Strip.

#### Resort Trams

Several resorts operate their own trams, like the [Aria Express](/Aria_Express), [Mandalay Bay Tram](/Mandalay_Bay_Tram), and the [Hard Rock-Treasure Island Tram](/Hard_Rock-Treasure_Island_Tram).

